Thank you again <@U9KA594Q3>, Actually I wanted to create a query  based on "Combination" variable. here is the solution I came up with.
```&lt;!-- Getting data from the contact record --&gt;
{% set Surface_Name = contact.surface_name|default('Concrete') %}
{% set Conditions = contact.conditions|default('Coated') %}
{% set Combination = contact.comabination_val|default('default')  %} 
{% set Finish_Name = contact.finish_name|default('Solid colour') %} 

&lt;!-- Hubdb Query --&gt;
{% if Combination == 'default' %} 
{% set prime_query = 'surface_type='~Surface_Name~'&amp;condition='~Conditions~'&amp;finish='~Finish_Name %}
{% else %}
{% set prime_query = 'surface_type='~Surface_Name~'&amp;condition='~Conditions~'&amp;combination='~Combination~'&amp;finish='~Finish_Name~''%}
{% endif %}```
I set the default value and based on that I passed the desired query.
